The paper deals with clustering of multi-view data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The proposed algorithm is designed to handle incomplete views and large-scale data, which are important challenges in real-world applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves optimization techniques and regularization methods, which are relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
